        Converts the input time series into a SAX data structure via sliding window and Z normalization.
        Parameters:
        ts - the input data.
        windowSize - the sliding window size.
        paaSize - the PAA size.
        cuts - the Alphabet cuts.
        nThreshold - the normalization threshold value.
        strategy - the NR strategy.
        Returns:
        SAX representation of the time series.

      • ts2saxViaWindowSkipping

        public SAXRecords ts2saxViaWindowSkipping(double[] ts,
                                          int windowSize,
                                          int paaSize,
                                          double[] cuts,
                                          NumerosityReductionStrategy strategy,
                                          double nThreshold,
                                          java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> skips)
        Converts the input time series into a SAX data structure via sliding window and Z normalization.
        Parameters:
        ts - the input data.
        windowSize - the sliding window size.
        paaSize - the PAA size.
        cuts - the Alphabet cuts.
        nThreshold - the normalization threshold value.
        strategy - the NR strategy.
        skips - The list of points which shall be skipped during conversion; this feature is particularly important when building a concatenated from pieces time series and junction shall not make it into the grammar.
        Returns:
        SAX representation of the time series.
